description:
&lt;p&gt;The Forensic Healthcare Service are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated administrator, who enjoys a challenge, to support the Hellingly Centre, a secure mental health unit near Hailsham, where you will be based.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have responsibility for providing a comprehensive range of administrative duties and will be responsible for supporting the on-going management of the Hellingly Centre rosters including liaison with staff, updating rostering systems and communicating rosters to the teams and be a central point of contact for the team to support filling shifts with bank staff at late notice, eg: due to staff sickness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A good knowledge of Microsoft office applications, in particular Excel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and organisation skills are essential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work well in a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have good interpersonal skills and are able to work in a confidential and sensitive manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the Allocate Health Roster system is desirable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Sharon Feakins&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Business Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Sharon.feakins@sussexpartnership.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0300 304 0698 or 07391415572&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
